pr_review_comment_body:
@tiborsimko 

> or they can do something like `docker exec -i -t --user root myapp_web_1 /bin/bash` and, when inside, then `apt-get install vim` as usual.

Not possible because the images are mounted read-only by default. I vote for installing `nano` as a neutral, minimal editor. Right now I'm using `sed` hacks as a work-around and it is really difficult to do file modifications (for config changes or when inserting trace-points in 3rd-party libraries).

I think that is better than just bailing out.

```python
if not six.PY3:
    try:
        formula_like = str(formula_like)
    except UnicodeEncodeError:
        raise PatsyError('...')
```
